<title>USA: Calnetics, Summa end merger pact.</title>
<headline>Calnetics, Summa end merger pact.</headline>
<dateline>CHATSWORTH, Calif 1997-05-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>Calnetics Corp said Wednesday that it and Summa Industries have mutually agreed to end their merger agreement.</p>
<p>Calnetics, a maker of components for the building materials, industrial plastics and agricultural irrigation industries, did not provide a reason for ending the pact.</p>
<p>&quot;We just mutually agreed that it was in our best interests to walk away,&quot; said Trygve Thoresen, general counsel for Calnetics.</p>
<p>Thoresen declined to comment further, and no one at Summa was immediately available to comment.</p>
<p>The companies had announced in March their plans to merge.</p>
